# Betterware Monorepo Project - Complete Overview

This is a monorepo project built with **Feature-Sliced Design (FSD)** architecture for Betterware Mini e-commerce.

## 🏗️ Architecture Summary

### Technology Stack for "web" application

- **Framework**: ReactJs 19.2.6
- **Language**: TypeScript 6.0.2
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS 4.3.0
- **Package Manager**: npm 11.6.1

### Technology Stack for "mobile" application

- **Framework**: React Native 0.86.0 with ReactJs 19.2.3
- **Language**: TypeScript 5.8.3
- **Styling**: Styled Components
- **Package Manager**: npm 11.6.1

### Core Architecture Pattern

**Feature-Sliced Design (FSD)** with strict layer hierarchy:

```
app ↑ pages ↑ widgets ↑ features ↑ entities ↑ shared
```

## 📁 Project Structure

### Architectural Architecture for "web" application

```
src/
├── app/               # Application initialization (providers, global styles, router)
├── pages/             # Page components mapping to application routes
├── widgets/           # Autonomous, composite UI blocks (e.g., Header, Sidebar)
├── features/          # User actions with business value (e.g., AddToCart, LoginByEmail)
├── entities/          # Business concepts and data models (e.g., User, Product, Order)
└── shared/            # Reusable infrastructure (UI kit, API clients, helpers)
```

### Architectural Architecture for "mobile" application

```
src/
├── app/          # App initialization: providers, global styles, global navigation root
├── pages/        # High-level screens or navigation entry points
├── widgets/      # Self-contained layout combinations (e.g., Feed, Header)
├── features/     # User actions bringing business value (e.g., AddToCart)
├── entities/     # Business domains, data structures, and states (e.g., User, Product)
└── shared/       # Cross-cutting, zero-dependency tools (e.g., UI primitives, theme, API clients)
```

### Standard Directory Setup for both "web" and "mobile" applications

```
src/entities/product/
├── ui/
│   ├── ProductCard.tsx       # Presentation logic
│   └── ProductRow.tsx
├── model/
│   ├── slice.ts              # Redux/Zustand state management
│   └── selectors.ts          # State selectors
├── api/
│   └── getProductById.ts     # Fetching logic
└── index.ts                  # Public API: export { ProductCard } from './ui/ProductCard'
```

